meaning_str.bing:
n. 英格兰；(泛指)英国；(泛指)英格兰和威尔斯
网络. 英格兰队；英伦；英格兰国家队

英格兰；(泛指)英国；(泛指)英格兰和威尔斯
英格兰队；英伦；英格兰国家队

1.en: and I said to myself, 'Perhaps I can get there with a boat. Perhaps I can get back to England one day.
1.cn: 我对自己说，“或许我用一只小船可以到达那儿。也许，有一天我便可以回到英格兰了。”

2.en: Yes. The Norman Conquest was the last successful invasion of England because England has never been invaded since.
2.cn: 是的，诺曼征服者是英格兰最后的侵略者，因为英格兰此后再也没被侵略过了

3.en: His tone, as his son always noted with pleasure, was that of the more luxuriant parts of New England.
3.cn: 正如他的儿子经常愉快地指出的，他说话仍带有新英格兰那种比较富饶的部分的腔调。

0.en: Oh, it's not just that, I would be England's most powerful weapon.
0.cn: 不只如此，我会是英格兰最强力的武器。

1.en: London is situated in the South-East of England in the Thames Valley.
1.cn: 伦敦位于英格兰的东南部，在泰晤士河上。

2.en: Another legacy of England's monarchy are the Royal Parks of London.
2.cn: 而伦敦皇家公园则是另一个英格兰皇室遗留下来的景点。

3.en: Yeah, when I got my 100th cap for England, he said, "You've done well, boy."
3.cn: 嗯，当我第100次身披英格兰战袍出战时，他说"你踢得不错，孩子"。

4.en: Of the many gifts England has given to the world, none has been greater than her language and literature.
4.cn: 英格兰为世界带来了很大的贡献，但最深远的莫过于它的语言和文学。

5.en: It would be a replica of a movie prop. Fair enough. It'd give you the right to rule a replica of England.
5.cn: 那肯定是电影道具的复制品。也有道理，那就是赋予你统治英格兰复制品的权力。

6.en: What did you have in mind? Well, off the top of my head, I'd have to go with Excalibur. It gives you the right to rule England.
6.cn: 那你想从哪把开始？我会不假思索地说亚瑟王的神剑，它能赋予你统治英格兰的权力。

7.en: Some years later, that nice young man from England was on his way home to see his little boy and was signing some autographs. For no particular reason at all, somebody shot him.
7.cn: 几年以后，那位从英格兰来的好年青人他回家去看他的孩子半路上在给人签名。完全没什么原因，有人枪杀了他。

8.en: Growing into one of the great medieval trading cities, she truly came of age in the 11th century, when William the Conqueror built the Tower of London, which was to become one of England's grimmest prisons.
8.cn: 此后，伦敦发展为中世纪一个庞大的贸易中心，而到了 11 世纪开始繁荣起来，当时威廉一世兴建的伦敦塔，是英格兰其中一所最为森严的监狱。

9.en: Yeah, but it's my whole life, you come to England.
9.cn: 但事关我的人生，你来英国。

10.en: No offense, but dating Kate Moss is like a law in England.
10.cn: 无意冒犯，但是貌似全英国男人都和凯特·摩斯交往过。

11.en: You stole my dream. I was going to conquer England some day.
11.cn: 你们偷走了我的梦想，我才是那个有一天要征服大英帝国的人。

12.en: When I was at university in England, my flatmate was from Texas.
12.cn: 我在英国读大学的时候，我室友是得克萨斯州人。

13.en: Hello. Hey. Oh my God. Ross, are you in England? Was Emily surprised?
13.cn: 天哪！你在英国吗？艾蜜莉惊喜吗？

14.en: Then she moved to England and she picked up this fake British accent.
14.cn: 后来她搬去英国了，还学了假惺惺的英国口音。

15.en: I am hours away from becoming the Queen of England. I know, it's a gas.
15.cn: 再过几个小时，我就是英国的女王了。我知道，太酷了。

16.en: We're just back from travelling, I want to see you while you're living in England.
16.cn: 我们刚旅游回来，想要看你在英国的生活。

17.en: Do you know who this is? Uh. The cockroach? This is Queen Elizabeth, ruler of England.
17.cn: 你们知道这是谁吗？呃，小强吗？这是伊丽莎白女王，英国统治者。

18.en: Mama. Now, if you'll excuse me, the prime minister of England needs her diaper changed.
18.cn: 妈妈。容我失陪一下，大英帝国首相的尿布该换了。

19.en: Oh, blimey! One of England's most famous myths has become a reality. As a new king has been crowned.
19.cn: 哦，天哪！英国最著名的神话之一，如今成为了现实，这就是刚刚加冕的新国王。
